*A glimpse of the canyon you get from [Cottonwood Canyon Road](/Cottonwood_Canyon_Road) as you crawl in from the south, having escaped the relative civilization of [U.S. Route 89](/U.S._Route_89_in_Utah). The road dutifully follows the watercourse for a stretch, because that's the path of least resistance. Then, apparently bored, it abandons the stream to trace an eroded geologic fault northward. A metaphor for something, probably.*

